@node "Intro" "Introduction"

  SignSelect is a very simple, but usefull tool, for those, who
  don't want to use the same signature everytime they send a
  mail. Of course many mail programms have the tagline feature
  (like Eucalyptus), but there's only one random line. So if you
  like to sign your mails with some witty comments, which are
  longer than a single line, you could either attach them by hand
  or use SignSelect to choose one or more jokes remarkes, or what-
  ever from your private and easy to setup @{"database file" link "Database"}.


  Back to @{"Index" link "Main"}
@endnode

@node "System" "System requirements"

  As this is a very very simple program there aren't many
  requirements:
  any Amiga (-;
  WB 3.x  maybe a lower version would work too, but I just don't
    bother about people who are still using Kick 2.0.
    Just try and tell @{"me" link "Author"}.

  Back to @{"Index" link "Main"}
@endnode

@node "Install" "Getting started"

  SignSelect can only be used from the cli.
  There are a few ways of installing. Either you put it in
  your user-startup - something like:

    c:SignSelect s:MyQuotes YAM:.signature 1

  Thats what I do, but it has the disadvantage, that the quotes
  only change on startup, so if you send 2 mails to the same user,
  without rebooting in the meantime (or starting signselect by hand)
  he will get the same quote both times.
  To avoid this, you could use a little skript to start Signselect
  everytime before you start your mail program:
  Something like:

    c:SignSelect s:MyQuotes YAM:.signature 1
    YAM:YAM

  Name this skript e.g. YAMStart and use it instead of starting YAM
  directly.

  Back to @{"Index" link "Main"}
@endnode

