@node "Usage" "Usage"

  First you have to set up a @{"database file" link "Database"}. Have a look at the
  example file included in this archive.
  The syntax of SignSelect is as simple, as could be:

  SignSelect <Databasefile, Outpufile, Number of quotes>

  The Databasefile is your private file with all the quotes you
  want to use.

  Outputfile should be the file your mailprogram uses as signature file
  e.g. YAM:.signature

  Number of quotes - O.K. I think you know, what that is.

  Back to @{"Index" link "Main"
@endnode

@node "Database" "The Database file"

  Just use your favorite text editor to write down the quotes
  you want to use. Directly after each quote you have to enter a
  #, so that SignSelect knows, where the quote ends. At the very end
  of the file enter the text you want to appear all the time. For
  example you name and email address.
  I think its best to look at the example database file included in
  this archive.

  Back to @{"Index" link "Main"}
@endnode

